# General Rules

Always generate production-ready code.

Never generate demo code.

Never generate placeholder logic.

Never generate fake APIs.

Never remove existing functionality.

Always preserve backward compatibility.

Prefer extending existing architecture.

Avoid unnecessary complexity.

Keep solutions modular.

Follow Single Responsibility Principle.

---

# Project Organization

Respect the current folder structure.

Do not move files unless requested.

Do not rename files.

Do not reorganize assets.

Keep HTML reusable.

Separate structure, style and behavior.

---

# HTML Rules

Prefer semantic HTML5.

Use accessible markup.

Use external CSS.

Use external JavaScript.

Never use inline JavaScript.

Avoid inline CSS.

Create reusable sections.

Keep layouts modular.

Optimize for future PHP conversion.

---

# CSS Rules

Prefer Bootstrap 5.

Use CSS variables.

Mobile-first.

Avoid !important.

Avoid duplicated selectors.

Keep components reusable.

---

# JavaScript Rules

Prefer ES2023+.

Use const by default.

Use async/await.

Avoid globals.

Keep modules independent.

---

# Images

Always use optimized images.

Lazy load where appropriate.

Use descriptive alt attributes.

---

# Accessibility

WCAG friendly.

Keyboard navigation.

Semantic HTML.

Proper labels.

Meaningful headings.

Visible focus states.

---

# Performance

Optimize for Core Web Vitals.

Avoid unnecessary JavaScript.

Avoid unnecessary DOM nodes.

Minimize HTTP requests.

Optimize assets.

---

# Security

Never expose credentials.

Validate all input.

Escape output.

Never hardcode secrets.

---

